since June 2012.  Since 2012, the U.S. national team has often played in larger [[Major League Soccer]] stadiums across the country. The Eagles have played a home match against a Tier 1 nation [[Mid-year rugby union tests|each June]] since 2012 before large crowds at [[BBVA Stadium]] in Houston, Texas.<ref>[http://texasrugbyunion.com/2012/03/06/its-official-usa-eagles-vs-italy/ \"It's Official: USA Eagles vs Italy\"], Texas Rugby Union.</ref> Since 2012, the Eagles have played at other MLS stadiums, such as [[Talen Energy Stadium]] in [[Delaware Valley|Philadelphia]] and the [[Dignity Health Sports Park]] in [[Los Angeles metropolitan area|Los Angeles]]. The Eagles play some of their less high-profile matches at minor league soccer stadiums.\n\nThe highest attended matches in the U.S. involving the U.S. national team are:<ref>[http://stats.espnscrum.com/scrum/rugby/records/team/highest_attendance.html?id=11;type=team Highest Attendance \u2013 United States of America], ESPN Scrum.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Rank !! Attendance !! Opponent !! width=90 | Date !! Venue !! Metro area\n|-\n| 1 || '''61,500''' || New Zealand || 2014-11-01 || [[Soldier Field]] (NFL) ||  Chicago, IL\n|-\n| 2 || '''30,051''' || [[M\u0101ori All Blacks]] || 2018-11-03 || [[Soldier Field]] (NFL) ||  Chicago, IL <ref name=\"rugbytoday.com\"/>\n|-\n| 3 || '''23,212''' || Australia || 2015-09-05 || [[Soldier Field]] (NFL) ||  Chicago, IL<ref>[http://en.espn.co.uk/scrum/rugby/story/273941.html \"Wallabies comfortable winners after improved performance in second half at Soldier Field\"], ESPN Scrum.</ref>\n|-\n| 4 || '''22,000''' || Ireland || 2017-06-10 || [[Red Bull Arena (New Jersey)|Red Bull Arena]] (MLS) || New York, NY<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2017/jun/10/keith-earls-ireland-usa-joey-carbery-injury \"Keith Earls leads Ireland past USA but fly-half Carbery is injury worry\"], ''Guardian'', June 10, 2017</ref>\n|-\n| 5 || '''20,181