[Papa Murphy's Park|Bonney Field]]{{efn|group=att|Now known as Papa Murphy's Park.}} (USL) || Sacramento, CA\n|-\n| 15 || '''10,241''' || [[Argentina XV national rugby union team|Argentina XV]] || 2016-02-06 || [[BBVA Stadium|BBVA Compass Stadium]]{{efn|group=att|name=BBVA}} (MLS) || Houston, TX\n|}\n\n;Notes\n{{notelist|group=att}}\n*The international rugby match in the U.S. with the largest crowd did not involve the United States national team; 62,000 watched Ireland defeat New Zealand 40\u201329 at Soldier Field on November 5, 2016.<ref>[http://www.news.com.au/sport/rugby/live-coverage-of-all-blacks-v-ireland-from-chicagos-soldier-field/news-story/46521ddbc332bb1fa18da359b04fa027 \"Inspired Ireland record first ever win over All Blacks at Chicago\u2019s Soldier Field\"], News.com.au, November 6, 2016.</ref>\n\n==Rivalry with Canada ==\n{{main|History of rugby union matches between Canada and United States}}\n\nThe United States' biggest rival in rugby is [[Canada national rugby union team|Canada]].  The US has played more test matches against Canada than any other country.  The two teams first met in 1977, and have played every year since then with the exception of 2010.  As of the end of 2019, the two sides have met 58 times, with 22 wins for the U.S., 38 wins for Canada, and 2 draws.\n\nThe U.S. and Canada routinely play each other in qualifying matches for the Rugby World Cup.  They have met in the qualification stages for every tournament, except for the 1987 tournament, for which teams were invited rather than going through qualification matches, and the 1995 tournament, for which Canada had automatically qualified by finishing as a quarterfinalist in the 1991 Rugby World Cup. Since 2015, the teams play each other annually at the [[Americas Rugby Championship]].\n\nThe U.S. has been undefeated in the last 12 matches, with 11 wins and a draw. The first victory of the Eagles' current unbeaten streak ended a seven-match winning streak by Canada that lasted from 2009 through 2013.\n\n==Tournament records==\n===Honors===\n*[[2018 Americas Rugby Championship]] \u2013 Champion\n*[[2017 Americas Rugby Championship]] \u2013 Champion\n*[[Rugby union at the 1924 Summer Olympics|1924 Olympics]] \u2013 Gold Medal\n*[[Rugby union at the 1920 Summer Olympics|1920 Olympics]] \u2013 Gold Medal\n\n===Rugby World Cup===\n{{main|United States at the Rugby World Cup}}\nThe United States has qualified for every [[Rugby World Cup]] except the 1995 tournament. The best result that the U.S. has managed at a Rugby World Cup is to win one game, which it accomplished in 1987, 2003, and again in 2011.\n\n{|class = \"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Tournament\n!Host\n!U.S. Win/Loss <br /> (Bonus Pts){{refn|group=o|A bonus point is awarded for scoring 4 tries or for losing by 7 points or less.}} \n!U.S. Finish\n! U.S. Defeated\n! Leading U.S. scorer\n|-\n| [[1987 Rugby World Cup|1987]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|AUS}}<br />{{Ru|NZL}}\n|1\u20132\n|3rd in Pool A\n| Japan (21\u201318)\n| [[Ray Nelson (rugby union)|Ray Nelson]] (24)\n|-\n| [[1991 Rugby World Cup|1991]]\n| align=left | {{ru|ENG}}<br />{{ru|FRA}}<br />{{ru|IRE}}<br />{{ru|SCO}}<br />{{ru|WAL}} \n|0\u20133\n|4th in Pool A\n| \u2014\n| [[Mark Williams (rugby player)|Mark Williams]] (16)\n|-\n| [[1995 Rugby World Cup|1995]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|RSA}}\n| colspan=4 | ''[[1995 Rugby World Cup \u2013 Americas qualification|Did not qualify]]''\n|-\n| [[1999 Rugby World Cup|1999]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|WAL}}\n|0\u20133\n|4th in Pool 5\n| \u2014\n| [[Kevin Dalzell]] (22)\n|-\n| [[2003 Rugby World Cup|2003]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|AUS}}\n|1\u20133 (2 BP)\n|4th in Pool B\n| Japan (39\u201326)\n| [[Mike Hercus]] (51)\n|-\n| [[2007 Rugby World Cup|2007]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|FRA}}\n|0\u20134 (1 BP)\n|5th in Pool A\n| \u2014\n| [[Mike Hercus]] (26)\n|-\n| [[2011 Rugby World Cup|2011]]\n| align=left | {{Ru|NZL}}\n|1\u20133 (0 BP)\n|4th in Pool C\n| Russia (13\u20136)\n| [[Chris Wyles]] (18)