as Rugby Championship|2019]] || 3\u20130-2 || 3rd || [[Joe Taufete'e]] (30) || Brazil, Canada, Chile \n|-\n|}\n\n===Summer Olympics===\n{{main|Rugby union at the Summer Olympics}}\nRugby was included an Olympic sport four times from 1900 to 1924, with the United States winning the last two of those tournaments \u2014 1920 and 1924. After a lengthy absence, rugby returned to the Summer Olympics in 2016, albeit in the [[rugby sevens]] format.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Olympics !! U.S. finish !! U.S. record !! Defeated\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagicon|FRA|1794}} [[Rugby union at the 1900 Summer Olympics|1900 Paris]]\n| colspan=3|''(U.S. did not participate)''\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagicon|UK|1801|size=23px}} [[Rugby union at the 1908 Summer Olympics|1908 London]]\n| colspan=3|''(U.S. did not participate)''\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Rugby union at the 1920 Summer Olympics|1920 Antwerp]]\n| bgcolor=gold | '''Gold'''\n| 1\u20130\n| France\n|-\n| align=left | {{flagicon|FRA|1794}} [[Rugby union at the 1924 Summer Olympics|1924 Paris]]\n| bgcolor=gold | '''Gold'''\n| 2\u20130\n| France, Romania\n|-\n|}\n\n===Defunct competitions===\n====Churchill Cup====\n{{Main|Churchill Cup}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; width: 60%; text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=8%| Year\n!width=25%| Host nation(s)\n!width=12%| U.S. record\n!width=13%| U.S. finish / <br /> # Teams\n|-\n|[[2003 Churchill Cup|2003]]\n| align=left | {{flagicon|CAN}} Canada\n|1\u20132\n| 2nd / 3\n|- style=\"background: #efefef;\"\n|[[2004 Churchill Cup|2004]]\n|  align=left | {{flagicon|CAN}} Canada\n|0\u20132\n|4th / 4\n|-\n|[[2005 Churchill Cup|2005]]\n|  align=left | {{flagicon|CAN}} Canada\n|1\u20131\n|3rd / 4\n|- style=\"background: #efefef;\"\n|[[2006 Churchill Cup|2006]]\n|  align=left | {{flagicon|CAN}} {{flagicon|USA}} Canada & United States \n|0\u20133\n| 6th / 6\n|-\n|[[2007 Churchill Cup|2007]]\n|  align=left | {{flagicon|ENG}} England\n