y 29, 2018.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Pts Diff !! width=80px | Result !! Opponent !! width=85px | Date\n|-\n| +14 || W (17\u20133) || align=left | {{ru|FRA}} || 1924-05-18\n|-\n| +8 || W (8\u20130) || align=left | {{ru|FRA}} || 1920-09-05\n|-\n| +1 || W (30-29) || align=left | {{ru|SCO}} || 2018-06-16\n|-\n| \u20133 || L (26\u201329) || align=left | {{ru|ARG}} || 1996-09-14\n|-\n| \u20133 || L (12\u201315) || align=left | {{ru|IRE}} || 2013-06-08\n|-\n| \u20134 || L (8\u201312) || align=left | {{ru|AUS}} || 1912-11-16\n|-\n| \u20134 || L (20\u201324) || align=left | {{ru|ITA}} || 2016-06-18\n|-\n| \u20135 || L (11-16) || align=left | {{ru|ARG}} || 1994-06-20\n|-\n| \u20135 || L (23-28) || align=left | {{ru|WAL}} || 1997-07-12\n|-\n| \u20136 || L (22-28) || align=left | {{ru|ARG}} || 1994-05-28\n|-\n|}\n\n==Other U.S. national teams==\n===USA Selects===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; width: 35%; text-align: center; float:right;\" \n|-\n|+ Americas Rugby Championship\n|-\n!width=6%|Year\n!width=17%|Champion\n!width=9%|U.S. result\n|-\n|[[2009 Americas Rugby Championship|2009]]\n| [[Argentina Jaguars]]\n|4th  \n|- style=\"background: #efefef;\"\n|[[2010 Americas Rugby Championship|2010]]\n| [[Argentina Jaguars]]\n|3rd  \n|-\n| 2011\n| colspan=3 | ''Not held due to the [[2011 Rugby World Cup]]''\n|-\n|[[2012 Americas Rugby Championship|2012]]\n| [[Argentina Jaguars]]\n|4th  \n|- style=\"background: #efefef;\"\n|[[2013 Americas Rugby Championship|2013]]\n| [[Argentina Jaguars]]\n|2nd  \n|-\n|[[2014 Americas Rugby Championship|2014]]\n| [[Argentina Jaguars]]\n|2nd  \n|-\n| 2015\n| colspan=3 | ''Not held due to the [[2015 Rugby World Cup]]''\n|-\n|}\n{{Main|USA Selects}}\n{{Update|section|date=January 2019}}\n\nThe USA Selects is a second national rugby team for the United States. The USA Selects is a developmental team, usually fielding younger players looking to break into the U.S. national team, and sometimes including amateur domestic U.S. national team players who need more high-level matches.\n\nThe USA Selects participates in the [[Americas Rugby Championship]], a tournament featuring the \"A\" sides for Argentina, Canada, the United States, and Uruguay. The ARC is an annual tournament that has been played every year since 2009 (except for Rugby World Cup years), and replaces the North America 4 competition. The USA Selects best result in the ARC was in 2013, when the USA Selects beat Canada A to take second place.<ref>[http://usarugby.org/mens-eagles-news/item/eagles-select-xvs-defeat-canada-30-10-at-americas-rugby-championship \"Eagles Select XVs defeat Canada 30-10 at Americas Rugby Championship\"], USA Rugby, October 15, 2013. Retrieved September 13, 2014.</ref>\n\n===Women's national team===\n{{Main|United States women's national rugby union team}}\nThe U.S. women's national team, officially formed in 1987, has been an international powerhouse since its inception, although more recently have fallen behind other powerhouses such as England and New Zealand on the [[Women's international rugby union#Women.27s Test Ranking|world rankings]]. The Eagles won the first official World Cup in 1991, and finished second in the two following World Cups (1994, 1998). The Eagles have set a high standard for international competition, leading an ensuing wave of women's rugby growth and game development worldwide.  The US finished 7th in the 2002 tournament.  The women's national team traveled to the United Kingdom in January 2006 to play Scotland, Ireland and England, winning all three games. The 2006 Women's Rugby World Cup was held in Edmonton, Canada.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Sports}}\n* [[Rugby union in the United States]]\n* [[USA Rugby]]\n* [[United States national rugby sevens team]]\n* [[United States national under-20 rugby union team]]\n* [[List of United States national rugby union players]]\n* [[Rugby World Cup]]\n* [[American Cougars]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|United States national rugby union team}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.usarugby.org/}}\n\n{{United States national rugby union team}}\n{{Rugby union in the United States}}\n{{USNationalTeams}}\n{{National rugby teams}}\n{{Churchill Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:United States National Rugby Union Team}}\n[[Category:North American national rugby union teams]]\n[[Category:United States national rugby union team| ]]\n[[Category:National sports teams of the United States|Rugby union]]\n", "name_user": "102.250.3.138", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_national_rugby_union_team"}
